         <abstract>
            <p>Whether to use the marginal cost of capital or the average cost of capital as the cut-off rate for the capital budgeting decision is not always explicitly stated in finance textbooks. In this article, the authors attempt to present in three ways how the correct cut-off rate is derived from the principle of maximizing shareholder wealth.</p>
